beats per minute to around 160 initially.

57
00:03:07,550 --> 00:03:10,630
You can see the access scale on your right
of the graph.

58
00:03:11,780 --> 00:03:16,430
It then should have plateaued there for a
while, since it was a set workload.

59
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:19,180
However, you can see that his core
temperature continued to rise and

60
00:03:19,180 --> 00:03:21,060
his heart rate did as well.

61
00:03:21,060 --> 00:03:25,220
By then end of 20 minutes, his heart rate
was over 190 beats per minute.

62
00:03:26,510 --> 00:03:29,750
Can you think back to why his heart rate
continued to rise?

63
00:03:31,580 --> 00:03:33,650
Cardiovasuclar drift.

64
00:03:33,650 --> 00:03:34,630
As he got hotter,

65
00:03:34,630 --> 00:03:39,250
more blood was shunted to the peripherate
in an unsuccessful attempt to cool him.

66
00:03:39,250 --> 00:03:40,836
So stroke volume was falling, and

67
00:03:40,836 --> 00:03:45,780
heart rate was compensating in order to
keep cardiac output sufficiently high.

68
00:03:45,780 --> 00:03:49,450
After exercise, Corey's heart rate fell as
expected, but rather than

69
00:03:49,450 --> 00:03:54,270
approaching baseline, it remained elevated
around 150 beats per minute.

70
00:03:54,270 --> 00:03:54,770
How come?

71
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:56,705
He was still hot.

72
00:03:56,705 --> 00:04:00,260
[LAUGH] Have you ever had that experience
where you're just sitting somewhere on

73
00:04:00,260 --> 00:04:04,030
a very hot day and your heart feels like
it's racing?

74
00:04:04,030 --> 00:04:05,700
Your heart rate is elevated to try and

75
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:08,860
send more blood to the skin for cooling,
and trying to compensate for

76
00:04:08,860 --> 00:04:12,030
the fall in stroke volume that we talked
about earlier.

77
00:04:12,030 --> 00:04:16,890
In Corey's case, post-exercise, he was
also a little bit dehydrated.

78
00:04:16,890 --> 00:04:19,500
Even though the sweat was not evaporating
through his suit,

79
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:24,380
he was still sweating up a storm, getting
quite wet inside his clothes.

80
00:04:24,380 --> 00:04:29,490
After the whole event, he was down about 1
kilo or 2.2 pounds of water weight.

